Rebuild Executive Briefing as 14-slide McKinsey storyline

Reorganize the briefing deck into four acts (Foundation, UAE Today,
Compare, Decide) so the user feels four sequential "wows": data is
real, UAE is understood, the world is comparable, the roadmap is clear.

Storyline & slide changes
- Replace Slide02_Brief with Slide02_Outline mapping the four acts to
  GPSSA's ambition, with an animated arrow connecting four chapter
  cards and a deliverable promise driven by the live slide count.
- Replace Slide05_WhereWeStand with Slide09_Quadrant: a Recharts
  scatter quadrant with mode toggle (Countries/Institutions), axis
  dropdowns, and a dynamic action sub-line.
- New Slide05_UAEToday: branches x coverage classes x mandate counters
  x governance architecture mosaic.
- New Slide06_Personas: 5x2 persona grid with expanding journey strip
  and idle spotlight, sourced from src/data/personas.ts.
- New Slide07_Atlas with AtlasRegionGrid: region-grouped maturity
  grid, hover scorecard, click-to-add comparator.
- New Slide13_Roadmap: 12-month roadmap deriving quarter from
  impact/effort with deterministic tie-break by strategicFit*feasibility.
- McKinsey-style action-header rewrites on Slide03_Compass,
  Slide04_Evidence (now an 8-tile wall with mandate + personas
  counters), and Slide10_PeerInstitutions.
- Rename existing slides for deck-order alignment:
  06->08 GlobalBenchmarks, 07->10 PeerInstitutions,
  08->11 ServiceChannelHeatmap, 09->12 Decision, 10->14 Closing.

Wiring
- Extend BriefingSnapshot with a MandateSection (statutory
  instruments, articles, milestones, source pages, obligation links,
  featured standards, latest milestones) populated by buildMandate()
  in snapshot.ts (mirrors /api/mandate/overview).
- Extract BRANCHES, COVERAGE_CLASSES, ARCHITECTURE, CONTROL_PILLARS
  into shared module src/data/mandateScope.ts; mandate dashboard pages
  now import from it.
- BriefingDeck registers the new 14-slide order; SlideEngine passes
  total to each renderer so Slide02_Outline and SlideChrome roll the
  count automatically.
- Comparator store reused: slide5 keys drive Quadrant, slide7 keys
  still drive Peers; no schema or migration changes.
- Fix pre-existing downlevel-iteration TS error in AtlasRegionGrid by
  switching Map.values() iteration to forEach.
